5/6inch-Experimental.preset_note:
***WARNING*** This preset REQUIRES Dynamic Gyro Filter ENABLED (cli: 'feature DYNAMIC_FILTER' or Configuration-Tab>Dynamic Filter>ON).
Experimental Work in Progress.
Here we retain a Gyro LPF and raise a single D-Term LPF for high-frequencies only (atypical), then depend on Dynamic Gyro Notch Filters and Dynamic D Term Notch Filters. Dynamic Filter MIN Hz and Static Gyro LPF cutoff Hz may need raising/tuning depending on aircraft. D-Term LPF1 cutoff Hz may need raising/tuning as well. In tests, D-LPF1 was raised to 220Hz and higher with success on 6-inch Apex-Clone. Pilot may consider setting D-LPF as PT2 to reduce D-Term noise or decreasing the Dynamic D-Term Notch Q value. It is the pilot's choice to disable Gyro LPF or not. Tests shown it flyable at the cost of increased noise and possibly motor heat. It is not recommended to turn off D-Term LPF's completely, but instead raise/tune as needed. Here, IMUF Q's are raised to more common values. Feathered-Pids is balanced at 50%. EmuBoosts are raised only sightly. iRelax values are decreased only slightly. This preset enables Axis-Lock, 2PASS, 2PASS-laziness, and Thrust-Linear are also enabled. Thrust-Linear may be un-calibrated to your motor specs. However with these settings, TPA is bypassed for better motor output control. TEST HOVER, TEST TEST TEST for Motor Heat; Err on side of safety please! Testing D-Term ABG was also successful (with high values), but remains off in this preset to minimize filter delay. This preset is experimental and may be removed in the future. This preset made by @nerdCopter in thanks to conversations with @GenXFPV, @dnlkrnwn, and @flickFPV. Also thanks to information from @Quickflash, @Andrey, and @DrSchnickistein. Feedback requested.
5/6inch-Experimental.__comment: *** Filters Gyro *** type: 0=PT1, 1=BiQuad, 2=PT2, 3=PT3, 4=PT4. Usually remain OFF/0 for Helio
*** Dynamic Gyro Filter ***; dynamic_filter variable is only a placeholder, does not act.

5inch-6S-2306-1950kv-DNLKRNWN-JuicyFruit.preset_note:
This tune is for maximum propwash handling and use minimum filtering, perfect for juicy smooth sbang.
WARNING: Dynamic Filter should be ON! WARNING: Gyro LPF is turned OFF here (atypical).
Minimum 5mm arm thickness is recommended,
TIPS: blackbox log first with debug_mode = gyro_scaled and check your motor/frame resonance peak noise. if your quad have more than 1 peak, you should add notch count to 3, and Q 350. Light weight quad with AUW under 500g, may need to lower P and D around 5-10%. Heavier quad with AUW 700gr and above might add P and D around 5-10%. Emu gravity is OFF, always check your quad CG manually.
5inch-6S-2306-1950kv-DNLKRNWN-JuicyFruit.__comment: *** Filters Gyro *** type: 0=PT1, 1=BiQuad, 2=PT2, 3=PT3, 4=PT4. Usually remain OFF/0 for Helio
*** Dynamic Gyro Filter ***; dynamic_filter variable is only a placeholder, does not act.

5inch-6S-2207-1950kv-ELRstrikefpv.preset_note:
This melody was realized to have a machine as reactive as possible, with no more propwash, and disabled Dynamic gyroscopic filter.
System requirements: softmount motor tpu, board on silicone gummies!! gyro icm20602 32 khz enabled, PID 8 khz.
The frame made 235 mm of motor to motor, the PID can be lowered slightly on the 215 mm safety frame.
After selecting the preset, go to the cli and copy this:
set pidsum_limit_yaw = 1000
set set gyro_32khz_hardware_lpf = EXPERIMENTAL
save
